- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper introduces a new circuit design for memristor emulation, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of non-von Neumann computing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper mentions potential applications of the memristor emulator circuit in neuromorphic computing, which falls under the scope of cs.NE. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper presents a hardware circuit design for memristor emulation, which can be categorized under cs.AR. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the memristor emulator circuit to a memcomputing application of maze solving, which can be considered a computational engineering problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of the memristor emulator circuit in chaotic circuits, which can be categorized under cs.SY.
